<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894c.111/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-20T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 20,
                                        1921—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>32. Your 22, January 12, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department approves note. Repeat text to Tokyo advising of Department’s
                            approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
